Grandpa records founder Noah Yusuf, alias Refigah, is among the list of aspirants who were cleared by IEBC to run for the Kibra MP seat. Refigah is vying on the DAP-K party under the Azimio la Umoja coalition. In a statement, Refigah said he is ready to walk together with the people to transform the community. "The journey to restore the lost glory of the Kibra constituency has officially commenced after I was cleared by IEBC today accompanied by my great supporters drawn from every village of Kibra," he said. "It's time to fix Kibra through servant leadership." He said he is guided by his vision and dream for Kibra residents. Refigah will be competing against Mwalimu Orero of ODM and former Harambee Stars striker Macdonald Mariga under UDA party.